Enum Modify

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Modify>
public enum Modify
extends java.lang.Enum<Modify>

This enum represents the 3 possible modifications a networked user can make to an event. NOTHING means no changes will be made. HEADER means only information in the event header (non-data) will possibly be modified. ANYTHING means that either header or data will possibly be modified. If the user gets events in which NOTHING will be modified, the server sends a copy of the event to the user over the network and immediately puts the originals back into the system. This greatly increases performance.

public static final Modify NOTHING
